rndApplications.name: rndApplications
rndApplications.description: The private MIB module definition for RND applications MIB.

rndAlarmEnabling.name: rndAlarmEnabling
rndAlarmEnabling.description: Indicates whether alarms should be issued to the high-level NMS

rndAlarmInterval.name: rndAlarmInterval
rndAlarmInterval.description: Indicates the minimal period of time which must pass after issuing an alarm before issuing the same alarm again.

rndMonitoredElementsTable.name: rndMonitoredElementsTable
rndMonitoredElementsTable.description: The table of monitored elements of the network

rndMonitoredElementEntry.name: rndMonitoredElementEntry
rndMonitoredElementEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rndMonitoredElementAddress.name: rndMonitoredElementAddress
rndMonitoredElementAddress.description: The IP address of the monitored element

rndMonitoredElementCommunity.name: rndMonitoredElementCommunity
rndMonitoredElementCommunity.description: The community of the monitored element

rndMonitoredElementLabel.name: rndMonitoredElementLabel
rndMonitoredElementLabel.description: The label assigned by the network manager to the monitored element

rndDefaultPollingInterval.name: rndDefaultPollingInterval
rndDefaultPollingInterval.description: The default period of time between two consecutive pollings of the monitored element for the value of an object instance. If no other polling interval is specifically assigned to the monitored object instance, this one will be used

rndDefaultLogFile.name: rndDefaultLogFile
rndDefaultLogFile.description: The default file path of the log-file which will contain the polling results for the monitored element. If no other file path is specifically assigned to the monitored object instance, this log-file will be used.

rndMonitoredElementStatus.name: rndMonitoredElementStatus
rndMonitoredElementStatus.description: It is used to manage the monitored elements table and indicates the current monitoring status of an element.

rndMonitoringTable.name: rndMonitoringTable
rndMonitoringTable.description: The table of monitored object instances. Each monitored object instance belongs to a monitored element previously entered in the rndMonitoredElementsTable.

rndMonitoringEntry.name: rndMonitoringEntry
rndMonitoringEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rndMonitoredElement.name: rndMonitoredElement
rndMonitoredElement.description: A label assigned by the network manager to a monitored element to which this monitored object instance belongs. This label must have been previously entered in an instance of rndMonitoredElementLabel

rndMonitoredObjectInstanceLabel.name: rndMonitoredObjectInstanceLabel
rndMonitoredObjectInstanceLabel.description: The label assigned by the network manager to the monitored object instance

rndMonitoredObjectName.name: rndMonitoredObjectName
rndMonitoredObjectName.description: The symbolic object type name of the object to which the monitored object instance belongs (as it appears the MIB module definition). In case of ambiguity the <MIB module name> : <object type name> format should be used. An instance of rndMonitoredObjectName need not be assigned any value, if the corresponding instance of rndMonitoredObjectIdentifier is assigned a value, since any one of these, together with the object instance identifier, suffices to unambigously identify the monitored object instance.

rndMonitoredObjectIdentifier.name: rndMonitoredObjectIdentifier
rndMonitoredObjectIdentifier.description: The object identifier of the object to which the monitored object instance belongs. An instance of rndMonitoredObjectIdentifier need not be assigned any value, if the corresponding instance of rndMonitoredObjectName is assigned a value, since any one of these, together with the object instance identifier, suffices to unambigously identify the monitored object instance.

rndMonitoredObjectInstance.name: rndMonitoredObjectInstance
rndMonitoredObjectInstance.description: The instance identifier (key) of the monitored object instance.

rndMonitoredObjectSyntax.name: rndMonitoredObjectSyntax
rndMonitoredObjectSyntax.description: The syntax of the monitored object instance (i.e., the syntax of the object type of the object to which the monitored instance belongs). Need not be assigned any value if the corresponding instance of rndMonitoredObjectName has been assigned a value

rndMonitoringInterval.name: rndMonitoringInterval
rndMonitoringInterval.description: The period of time between two consecutive retrievals of the monitored object instance's value.

rndAlarmMaxTreshold.name: rndAlarmMaxTreshold
rndAlarmMaxTreshold.description: The value of the monitored object instance, the exceeding of which will cause the generation of an alarm to the high-level management station.

rndAlarmMinTreshold.name: rndAlarmMinTreshold
rndAlarmMinTreshold.description: If the value of the monitored object instance falls below the value assigned to rndAlarmMinTreshold, an alarm to the high-level management station will be issued.

rndMonitoringLogfile.name: rndMonitoringLogfile
rndMonitoringLogfile.description: The entire path of the file in which the results of the monitoring of this object instance should be recorded.

rndMonitoringEntryStatus.name: rndMonitoringEntryStatus
rndMonitoringEntryStatus.description: It is used to manage the monitored object instances table and indicates the current monitoring status of an object instance.

rndMibFilesTable.name: rndMibFilesTable
rndMibFilesTable.description: The table of monitored object instances. Each monitored object instance belongs to a monitored element previously entered in the rndMonitoredElementsTable.

rndMibFileEntry.name: rndMibFileEntry
rndMibFileEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rndMibFileIndex.name: rndMibFileIndex
rndMibFileIndex.description: The number of the MIB file in the list MIB files supported by the Mid-Level management station. The order of the MIB files in this list must reflect the the IMPORT relation between the MIBS contained in the MIB files, i.e., if MIB A IMPORTS FROM MIB B, the file containing MIB A must have a lesser index in this table than the file containing MIB B.

rndMibFilePath.name: rndMibFilePath
rndMibFilePath.description: The path of the MIB file in the MIB file server.

rndMibFileRefresh.name: rndMibFileRefresh
rndMibFileRefresh.description: Indicates if the file should be fetched after setting this entry from the MIB file server.

rndMibFileEntryStatus.name: rndMibFileEntryStatus
rndMibFileEntryStatus.description: It is used to manage the MIB files table.

rndHardwareConfiguration.name: rndHardwareConfiguration
rndHardwareConfiguration.description: Indicates whether the current SET SNMP PDU contains hardware configuration (i.e., normally read-only variables). SET of such variables in the Mid-level management station will be allowed only if this variable is included in the SNMP PDU and its value is true. Its value as returned in a GET SNMP PDU will always be false.

rndEraseSimulatedConfiguration.name: rndEraseSimulatedConfiguration
rndEraseSimulatedConfiguration.description: eraseSimulatedConfiguration instructs the MLNMS to erase all the simulated configuration from its configuration data-base (CDB). This the only accepted value for SNMP SET statements and will never be returned in SNMP GET statements. simulatedConfigurationPresent indicates that the MLNMS currently has a simulated configuration. simulatedConfigurationErased indicates that the MLNMS currently has no simulated configuration.

rndDeleteValuesTable.name: rndDeleteValuesTable
rndDeleteValuesTable.description: This table indicates which MIB variables are row status fields which control the status of the entry to which they belong. This table also indicates which (integer!) value of these MIB variables will cause, if present in a SNMP SET PDU, the deletion of the conceptual row instance to which the SET MIB variable instance belongs.

rndDeleteValuesEntry.name: rndDeleteValuesEntry
rndDeleteValuesEntry.description: The row definition for the rndDeleteValuesTable table.

rndRowStatusVariableName.name: rndRowStatusVariableName
rndRowStatusVariableName.description: The name of the row status field. This name may not necessarily be any name which is present in the MIBs loaded into the MLNMS station.

rndRowStatusObjectId.name: rndRowStatusObjectId
rndRowStatusObjectId.description: The object id of the row status field. If the rndRowStatusVariableName is a name present in the MIBs loaded into the MLNMS, this MIB variable is not required, but if given, it must match the object id known to the MLNMS. The variable identified by rndRowStatusVariableName and/or rndRowStatusObjectId must be a read-write MIB variable of type INTEGER which belongs to an entry (i.e, is a child of a MIB variable of type SEQUENCE).

rndRowDeleteValue.name: rndRowDeleteValue
rndRowDeleteValue.description: The value of the variable identified by rndRowStatusVariableName and/or rndRowStatusObjectId, which, if present in a SNMP SET PDU, will cause the deletion of the conceptual row instance which the SET MIB variable instance belongs.

rndDeleteValueEntryStatus.name: rndDeleteValueEntryStatus
rndDeleteValueEntryStatus.description: It is used to delete an entry from this table.

rndSimulatedVariablesTable.name: rndSimulatedVariablesTable
rndSimulatedVariablesTable.description: This table indicates which MIB variables are simulated.

rndSimulatedVariablesEntry.name: rndSimulatedVariablesEntry
rndSimulatedVariablesEntry.description: The row definition for the rndSimulatedVariablesTable table.

rndSimulatedVariableObjectId.name: rndSimulatedVariableObjectId
rndSimulatedVariableObjectId.description: The object id of the simulated variable. If the simulated variable belongs to a table entry, the entire entry is henceforth supported.

rndSimulatedVariableEntryStatus.name: rndSimulatedVariableEntryStatus
rndSimulatedVariableEntryStatus.description: It is used to delete an entry from this table.

rndSnmpTestPassword.name: rndSnmpTestPassword
rndSnmpTestPassword.description: This variable enables the user supplying the correct code to use the SNMP test feature.

rndSnmpTests.name: rndSnmpTests
rndSnmpTests.description: This variable enables the authorized user to test various SNMP features.

rndSimulateUndo.name: rndSimulateUndo
rndSimulateUndo.description: This variable enables the authorized user to test the SNMP UNDO feature.

rlSnmpServTestRequest.name: rlSnmpServTestRequest
rlSnmpServTestRequest.description: This variable enables the authorized user to test the SNMP SERV package.

rlSnmpServTestResponse.name: rlSnmpServTestResponse
rlSnmpServTestResponse.description: This variable enables the authorized user to retrieve the results of a the SNMP SERV package test.

rlSnmpServCreateTestPool.name: rlSnmpServCreateTestPool
rlSnmpServCreateTestPool.description: This variable enables the authorized user to indicate that after its reset the device should create a buffer pool for SNMPServ process PDU testing.

rlSnmpServITCbindClients.name: rlSnmpServITCbindClients
rlSnmpServITCbindClients.description: This variable enables the authorized user to to indicate that after its reset the device should create ITC clients for SnmpServ data requests clients. The semantics of this variable is as follows: subidentifier 2*n indicates whether the client n is synchronous(1) or asynchronous(2) subidentifier 2*n+1 indicates the number of simulatneous requests expected by client n.

rlMibTreeTable.name: rlMibTreeTable
rlMibTreeTable.description: This reflects the MIB tree of the device.

rlMibTreeEntry.name: rlMibTreeEntry
rlMibTreeEntry.description: Each row shows a tree relationsship in the MIB.

rlMibTreeFather.name: rlMibTreeFather
rlMibTreeFather.description: The father in a tree relation ship.

rlMibTreeSon.name: rlMibTreeSon
rlMibTreeSon.description: The son in a tree relation ship.

rlMibTreeSonObjectId.name: rlMibTreeSonObjectId
rlMibTreeSonObjectId.description: The object identifier of the son in a tree relation ship.

rlMibTreeGrandFather.name: rlMibTreeGrandFather
rlMibTreeGrandFather.description: The grand father (i.e father's father) in a tree relation ship.

PingCompletionStatus.name: PingCompletionStatus
PingCompletionStatus.description: If all the echo request packets in this sequence have been responded by valid echo responses, this object is set to ok. Otherwise this status indicates the problem. bad-reply-data indicates that the reply data is not equal to the response data.

rsPingTable.name: rsPingTable
rsPingTable.description: A table of ping request entries.

rsPingEntry.name: rsPingEntry
rsPingEntry.description: A ping request entry. A management station wishing to create an entry should first generate a pseudo-random serial number to be used as the index to this sparse table. It must also create in the same PDU the associated instance of the address object. It should also modify in the same PDU the default values for the other configuration objects if the defaults are not appropriate. Once the sequence completes, the management station should retrieve the values of the status objects of interest, and should then delete the entry. In order to prevent old entries from clogging the table, entries will be aged out, but an entry will never be deleted within 5 minutes of completing.

rsPingAddress.name: rsPingAddress
rsPingAddress.description: The address of the device to be pinged. Once an instance of this object is created, its value can not be changed.

rsPingPacketCount.name: rsPingPacketCount
rsPingPacketCount.description: Specifies the number of ping packets to send to the target in this sequence.

rsPingPacketSize.name: rsPingPacketSize
rsPingPacketSize.description: Specifies the size of ping packets to send to the target in this sequence. The lower and upper boundaries of this object are implementation dependent.

rsPingPacketTimeout.name: rsPingPacketTimeout
rsPingPacketTimeout.description: Specifies the amount of time to wait for a response to a transmitted packet before declaring the packet 'dropped.'

rsPingDelay.name: rsPingDelay
rsPingDelay.description: Specifies the minimum amount of time to wait before sending the next packet in a sequence after receiving a response. The actual delay may be greater due to internal task scheduling.

rsPingTrapOnCompletion.name: rsPingTrapOnCompletion
rsPingTrapOnCompletion.description: Specifies whether or not a rsPingCompletion trap should be issued on completion of the sequence of pings. If such a trap is desired, the NMS should ensure that the community table contains an instance specified by the NMSs IP address with rndCommunityTrapsEnable = trapsEnable.

rsPingSentPackets.name: rsPingSentPackets
rsPingSentPackets.description: The number of ping packets that have been sent to the target in this sequence.

rsPingReceivedPackets.name: rsPingReceivedPackets
rsPingReceivedPackets.description: The number of ping packets that have been received from the target in this sequence.

rsPingMinReturnTime.name: rsPingMinReturnTime
rsPingMinReturnTime.description: The minimum round trip time of all the packets that have been sent in this sequence. The value returned to a GET request is meaningless if no ping response in a sequence has been received yet.

rsPingAvgReturnTime.name: rsPingAvgReturnTime
rsPingAvgReturnTime.description: The average round trip time of all the packets that have been sent in this sequence.The value returned to a GET request is meaningless if no ping response in a sequence has been received yet.

rsPingMaxReturnTime.name: rsPingMaxReturnTime
rsPingMaxReturnTime.description: The maximum round trip time of all the packets that have been sent in this sequence.The value returned to a GET request is meaningless if no ping response in a sequence has been received yet.

rsPingCompletionStatus.name: rsPingCompletionStatus
rsPingCompletionStatus.description: If all the echo request packets in this sequence have been responded by valid echo responses, this object is set to ok. Otherwise this status indicates the problem. bad-reply-data indicates that the reply data is not equal to the response data.

rsPingTimeStamp.name: rsPingTimeStamp
rsPingTimeStamp.description: The time-stamp indicating the time and date of creation or last update of this request. The format of the time-stamp is dd/mm/yyyy hh:mm:ss

rsPingEntryStatus.name: rsPingEntryStatus
rsPingEntryStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

rsPingInetTable.name: rsPingInetTable
rsPingInetTable.description: A table of ping request entries.

rsPingInetEntry.name: rsPingInetEntry
rsPingInetEntry.description: A ping request entry. A management station wishing to create an entry should first generate a pseudo-random serial number to be used as the index to this sparse table. It must also create in the same PDU the associated instance of the address object. It should also modify in the same PDU the default values for the other configuration objects if the defaults are not appropriate. Once the sequence completes, the management station should retrieve the values of the status objects of interest, and should then delete the entry. In order to prevent old entries from clogging the table, entries will be aged out, but an entry will never be deleted within 5 minutes of completing.

rsPingInetAddressType.name: rsPingInetAddressType
rsPingInetAddressType.description: The address type of the device to be pinged. Once an instance of this object is created, its value can not be changed.

rsPingInetAddress.name: rsPingInetAddress
rsPingInetAddress.description: The address of the device to be pinged. Once an instance of this object is created, its value can not be changed.

rsPingInetPacketCount.name: rsPingInetPacketCount
rsPingInetPacketCount.description: Specifies the number of ping packets to send to the target in this sequence.

rsPingInetPacketSize.name: rsPingInetPacketSize
rsPingInetPacketSize.description: Specifies the size of ping packets to send to the target in this sequence. The lower and upper boundaries of this object are implementation dependent.

rsPingInetPacketTimeout.name: rsPingInetPacketTimeout
rsPingInetPacketTimeout.description: Specifies the amount of time (in milliseconds) to wait for a response to a transmitted packet before declaring the packet 'dropped.'

rsPingInetDelay.name: rsPingInetDelay
rsPingInetDelay.description: Specifies the minimum amount of time (in milliseconds) to wait before sending the next packet in a sequence after receiving a response. The actual delay may be greater due to internal task scheduling.

rsPingInetTrapOnCompletion.name: rsPingInetTrapOnCompletion
rsPingInetTrapOnCompletion.description: Specifies whether or not a rsPingCompletion trap should be issued on completion of the sequence of pings. If such a trap is desired, the NMS should ensure that the community table contains an instance specified by the NMSs IP address with rndCommunityTrapsEnable = trapsEnable.

rsPingInetSentPackets.name: rsPingInetSentPackets
rsPingInetSentPackets.description: The number of ping packets that have been sent to the target in this sequence.

rsPingInetReceivedPackets.name: rsPingInetReceivedPackets
rsPingInetReceivedPackets.description: The number of ping packets that have been received from the target in this sequence.

rsPingInetMinReturnTime.name: rsPingInetMinReturnTime
rsPingInetMinReturnTime.description: The minimum round trip time (in milliseconds) of all the packets that have been sent in this sequence. The value returned to a GET request is meaningless if no ping response in a sequence has been received yet.

rsPingInetAvgReturnTime.name: rsPingInetAvgReturnTime
rsPingInetAvgReturnTime.description: The average round trip time (in milliseconds) of all the packets that have been sent in this sequence.The value returned to a GET request is meaningless if no ping response in a sequence has been received yet.

rsPingInetMaxReturnTime.name: rsPingInetMaxReturnTime
rsPingInetMaxReturnTime.description: The maximum round trip time (in milliseconds) of all the packets that have been sent in this sequence.The value returned to a GET request is meaningless if no ping response in a sequence has been received yet.

rsPingInetCompletionStatus.name: rsPingInetCompletionStatus
rsPingInetCompletionStatus.description: If all the echo request packets in this sequence have been responded by valid echo responses, this object is set to ok. Otherwise this status indicates the problem. bad-reply-data indicates that the reply data is not equal to the response data.

rsPingInetTimeStamp.name: rsPingInetTimeStamp
rsPingInetTimeStamp.description: The time-stamp indicating the time and date of creation or last update of this request. The format of the time-stamp is dd/mm/yyyy hh:mm:ss

rsPingInetEntryStatus.name: rsPingInetEntryStatus
rsPingInetEntryStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

rsPowerSupplyRedundacyEntry.name: rsPowerSupplyRedundacyEntry
rsPowerSupplyRedundacyEntry.description: The status of power supply redundancy for this table.

rsPowerSupplyRedundacyReNumber.name: rsPowerSupplyRedundacyReNumber
rsPowerSupplyRedundacyReNumber.description: This number identifies the module backed up by power supply redundancy in the stack.

rsPowerSupplyRedundacyStatus.name: rsPowerSupplyRedundacyStatus
rsPowerSupplyRedundacyStatus.description: The status of a power supply redundancy of the entry.

rsEraseNvramAfterReset.name: rsEraseNvramAfterReset
rsEraseNvramAfterReset.description: The name of NVRAM application that will be erased after reset or ALL if all NVRAM should be erased.

rsNvramApplEntry.name: rsNvramApplEntry
rsNvramApplEntry.description: The status of NVRAM application table.

rsNvramApplIndex.name: rsNvramApplIndex
rsNvramApplIndex.description: The index of NVRAM application table.

rsNvramApplName.name: rsNvramApplName
